Why Jquery??
-open source,lib.
-Rapid development.
-server side 
-lightweight,cross browser & css3.0.
-support AJAX capabilties,event handling,animation effects.
-wide range of plug-in availabe.

**********************************************
JQuery Syntax:
$(html element or selector).action()
selector-  To find HTML element(s)
action()- Action to be performed on the element(s).
e.g $("p")
    $("#p1")    -ID 
    $(".test") -class
e.g 
$(this).hide()      -hides the current element
$("p").hide()       -hides all element with class="test"
$(".test").remove() -removes all the elements with class="test"
$("#test").remove() -removes the element with id="test"

doucument.getElementbyId("").value
Document.getElementbyTagname("p")


<script>
$("p").hide()
</script>
ready event=doucument
<script>
    $(doucument).ready(function(){
        $("p").hide();
    })
</script>

*****************************************
Its prevents any jQuery code from running before the doucment is finshed.
**************************************
Callback function

Callback is a refernce to excecutable code, or a piece of excutable code,
that is passed an argurment to the other function.

*****************************************************
DOM in JQuery

doucment.
$().

text()-Sets or returns the text content of selected elements.
Val()-Sets or returns the value of form fields
attr()-It is used to set or change attribute values.
append()-Inserts content at the end of the selected element.
prepend()-Inserts content at the starrt of the selected element.
remove()-Removes the selected element(and its child element).

